nhc_headline: ...AIR FORCE HURRICANE HUNTERS INDICATE HUMBERTO REMAINS A CATEGORY 4 HURRICANE... ...DANGEROUS SURF WILL AFFECT BERMUDA AND MOST OF THE U.S. EAST COAST THIS WEEK...
summary: ...AIR FORCE HURRICANE HUNTERS INDICATE HUMBERTO REMAINS A CATEGORY 4 HURRICANE... ...DANGEROUS SURF WILL AFFECT BERMUDA AND MOST OF THE U.S. EAST COAST THIS WEEK... As of 11:00 PM AST Sun Sep 28 the center of Humberto was located near 26.2, -66.2 with movement NW at 14 mph. The minimum central pressure was 928 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 140 mph.
